This paper deals with image generation using generative adversarial networks (GANs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes novel families of GANs, which involves redesigning the generator prior and objective function, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses information theory, which is a topic in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
